solutions.content:
**Approach:**

* if we rob the ith level then we can't rob the i+1 th level and hence we move to the (i+2)th level
	* ```ans = root->val + rob(root->left->left) + rob(root->left->right) + rob(root->right->left) + rob(root->right->right)```
* if we don't rob the ith level then we move to the (i+1)th level
	* ```ans = rob(root->left) + rob(root->right)```
* final ans will be the maximum of above two cases


**Brute force:**

```
class Solution
{
public:
    int rob(TreeNode *root)
    {
        if (root == NULL)
            return 0;
        int val = 0;
        if (root->left != NULL)
            val += rob(root->left->left) + rob(root->left->right);
        if (root->right != NULL)
            val += rob(root->right->left) + rob(root->right->right);
        int notrob = rob(root->left) + rob(root->right);
        int rob = val + root->val;
        return max(notrob, rob);
    }
};
```

* we can observe that there are some repetitive calls in the above code and that's why it gives TLE
* so we can just store the optimal answer we get for each node in a map
* return the value if it has been already computed
* otherwise follow the same approach
* in the below code,
	* x = notrob case
	* y = rob the root case



**DP**

```
class Solution
{
public:
    unordered_map<TreeNode *, int> mp;
    int rob(TreeNode *root)
    {
        if (root == NULL)
            return 0;
        if (mp.find(root) != mp.end())
            return mp[root];
        mp[root] = -1;
        int x = rob(root->left) + rob(root->right);
        int y = root->val;
        if (root->left != NULL)
            y += rob(root->left->left) + rob(root->left->right);
        if (root->right != NULL)
            y += rob(root->right->left) + rob(root->right->right);
        mp[root] = max(x, y);
        return mp[root];
    }
};
```

* we can see that we only have two options at each node either rob the node or not
* if we rob the root
	* then we don't want to rob the left and right child
	* ```ans = root->val + leftnotrob+ rightnotrob```
* if we don't rob the root
	* we will check what's the best case for the left and right child, whether to rob them or not
	* ```ans = max(leftnotrob, leftrob) + max(rightnotrob, rightrob```
* store these values in a pair to handle repetitive calls
* ```pair = {notrob,rob}```


**DP-space optimized:**

```
class Solution
