***Simple Approach:-***
As theif cannot enter two directly connected house, so he cannot enter root and its children. So, he has only two options :
1. Either he enter the **root and its grandchildren**.
2. Or he enter the **children only**.

Lets write the recursive solution.

We will use pair (**pair<int,int> t**) to store answer :
1. **root value**+**sum of grandchildren** in **t.first** and
2. **sum of children** in **t.second**
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/a50cae51-7559-4181-8256-e48012c14957_1638731240.4278634.jpeg)


```
class Solution {
public:

    pair<int,int> solve(TreeNode* root){
        if(root == NULL)
            return {0,0};

        pair<int,int> l = solve(root->left);
        pair<int,int> r = solve(root->right);

        pair<int,int> t;

        //here l.second + r.second = Sum of grandchildren and l.first + r.first = Sum of children
        //t.first contains maxmium money theif can rob till this house(node)
        t.first = max(root->val + l.second + r.second, l.first + r.first);

        //t.second contains the sum of children
        t.second = l.first + r.first;

        return t;
    }

    int rob(TreeNode* root) {
        return solve(root).first;
    }
};
```
