solutions.content:
To solve these type of questions we have to consider two cases.
01. To choose the current node in our optimal solution.
02. To not choose the current node in our optimal solution.

Simple isn't it? If not don't worry read till end.

Suppose the robber had robbed the root house then he can't rob the left and right house. right??
So this lies in the first case. To maximize his robbery he will look for next possible houses to rob, which will .....???? guess guess.... Ok those will be left and right child of the left child of root and left and right child of the right child of root. Confusing?? See the image.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/7e290b71-6a11-4889-84e9-7b5f698c9ac4_1642224789.9577794.jpeg)

We will rob the houses colored in green. So the final answer will be 3 + 1 + 3 + 1 = 8. So this is the ans of the first case (see above cases) where we chose to rob the root house.

Now we will calculate the case where we won't choose to rob the root house. In this case we will rob both left and right child of root and calculate the below tree solution of these subtrees as well. See image.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/78ae814b-38e3-478e-8dfe-e6481311715d_1642225086.7021086.jpeg)

in this case our answer will be 4+5 = 9, when we don't choose the root house to rob.

Now we have to choose the maximum of both case and return it. Clearly the maximum is 9 in case when we don't choose the root house and thats our answer. :)

Also to avoide similar subproblem calculation we will use unordered map to store solutions of subproblems. 

See the code below. If you like my explanation please upvote. Thanks.

```
class Solution {
public:
    unordered_map<TreeNode*, int> dp;
    int rob(TreeNode* root) {
        if(root == NULL) return 0;

        if(dp.count(root)) return dp[root];
        int incRoot = root->val, excRoot = 0;

        if(root -> left != NULL){
            incRoot += rob(root -> left -> left);
            incRoot += rob(root -> left -> right);
        } 

        if(root -> right != NULL){
            incRoot += rob(root -> right -> left);
            incRoot += rob(root -> right -> right);
        } 

        excRoot += rob(root -> left);
        excRoot += rob(root -> right);

        return dp[root] = max(incRoot, excRoot);  
    }
};

