solutions.content:
`dfs` function returns two values, the max amount of money with and without this node.
After `return`, The first one will become OneLayer variable and can't be accumulated with this node.
The second one will become TwoLayer variable and can be used for accumulating with or without this node.

When under the condition we calculate the max amount of money without this node, we can't use OneLayer and TwoLayer at the same time, so we choose max(onelayer, twolayer) for left and right nodes.
```
class Solution:
    def rob(self, root: Optional[TreeNode]) -> int:
        def dfs(node):
            leftOneLayer, leftTwoLayer, rightOneLayer, rightTwoLayer = [0] * 4
            if node.left:
                leftOneLayer, leftTwoLayer = dfs(node.left)
            if node.right:
                rightOneLayer, rightTwoLayer = dfs(node.right)
            if not node.left and not node.right:
                return node.val, 0

            return node.val + leftTwoLayer + rightTwoLayer, max(leftOneLayer, leftTwoLayer) + max(rightOneLayer, rightTwoLayer)
        return max(dfs(root))
```

