```
class Solution {
    /*
        this is a typical  tree dp problem, very similar to the hard one 
        binary tree camera.
        It used the idea of divide and conquer with a time complexity of O(n).
        We let ans[0] and ans[1] to be the maxmoney we can get when we
        choose/not choose the current house. 
        l[0] and l[1] to be the maxmoney we can get when we choose/not choose the current house's left child. 
        r[0] and r[1] to be the maxmoney we can get when we choose/not choose the current house's right child.
        Hence we can deduce that the dp equation to be:
        ans[0] = l[1] + r[1] + root.val;
        ans[1] = max(l[1] + r[1], l[0] + r[0], l[0] + r[1], l[1] + r[0]);

        final answer is max(ans[0], ans[1]).
    */
    public int rob(TreeNode root) {
        int[] ans = solve(root);
        return Math.max(ans[0], ans[1]);
    }

    private int[] solve(TreeNode root) {
        int[] ans = new int[2];
        if (root == null) {
            ans[0] = 0;
            ans[1] = 0;
            return ans;
        }

        int[] l = solve(root.left);
        int[] r = solve(root.right);
        ans[0] = l[1] + r[1] + root.val;
        ans[1] = Math.max(Math.max(Math.max(l[1] + r[1], l[0] + r[1]), 
                                   l[1] + r[0]),l[0] + r[0]);
        return ans;
    }
}
```

