solutions.content:
The idea is pretty similar as those of previous House Robber problems. We can use an unordered_map called `value` to record the max value we can get from the binary tree rooted at it.

For a specific node **root**, the max value we can get from the binary tree rooted at it is either:

rob **root**, added with the max value we can get from **two children of root->left** and **two children of root->right**, which means  (assuming both root->left and root->right are not NULL)

    value[root] = root->val + value[root->left->left] + value[root->left->right] + value[root->right->left] + value[root->right->right]


or,


do not rob root, add the max value we can get from **root->left** and **root->right**, which means 

    value[root] = value[root->left] + value[root->right]




We can traverse the tree in post-order so that when we calculate value[root], the value of all its children is known. We could use a stack to store all the nodes. `cur` is the currently processed node while `pre` is the previous node processed. We keep pushing **cur**'s left child into stack until it becomes NULL, then set **cur** to the top of stack. If **cur->right** is NULL or it's processed before, since **cur**'s left child is already processed, which means all the children of cur are processed, therefore we can calculate value[cur] now. If not, just set cur = cur->right. Finally, just return value[root].



    class Solution {
    public:
        int rob(TreeNode* root) {
            unordered_map<TreeNode*, int> value;
            stack<TreeNode*> s;
            TreeNode *cur, *pre;
            value[NULL] = 0;
            for(cur = root, pre = NULL; !s.empty() || cur != NULL; ) {
                while(cur != NULL) {
                    s.push(cur);
                    cur = cur->left;
                }
                cur = s.top();
                if(cur->right == NULL || cur->right == pre) {
                    value[cur] = max(value[cur->left] + value[cur->right], cur->val + (cur->left == NULL ? 0 : value[cur->left->left] + value[cur->left->right]) + (cur->right == NULL ? 0 : value[cur->right->left] + value[cur->right->right]));
                    pre = cur;
                    cur = NULL;
                    s.pop();
                }
                else
                    cur = cur->right;
            }

            return value[root];
        }
    };

