so for this array if we try to build a dp array it will look something like this dp - [1,2,4,4]
at ith index dp[i] means the maximum sum till now either by choosing ith value in array or not  and we are not selecting adjacent values
arr = [1,2,3,1]
dp = [1,2,4,4]
so at ith index dp[i] = max(dp[i-1] , dp[i-2]+arr[i])
you can use dp[i-2] along with current value or simply use dp[i-1] , sumply return max of both
using same in the tree , if we reaches any null root simply return {0,0} and at every node we just need to store 2 values in the array - maximum sum till now if we chooses current node , maximum sum till now if we don't choose current node.
by the combination of these two values we can simply calculate max sum till now by following the rule not to choose adjacent values


