# Approach (Bruteforce)
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
A Toeplitz matrix is a matrix where every left-to-right descending diagonal has the same element. 
The algorithm checks if all elements in each row are equal to their corresponding elements in the previous row, starting from column 1.


# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n^2)$$  We have used 2 loops here.
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$ No Extra Space is used. here
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
