Sorry for the atrocious title. After getting AC, i checked other people's code and it turned out to be way simpler than I thought. 

Basically I checked every diagonal in the matrix - diagonal by diagonal.
This is also called gap method or the diagonal traversal of the matrix which is a pretty common trick in DP problems. 
In the gap method, we utilise the fact that in every diagonal of a matrix there is a constant between the row and column index.

Here is code if anyone is interested

```
public class Solution {
    /**
     * @param matrix: the given matrix
     * @return: True if and only if the matrix is Toeplitz
     */
    public boolean isToeplitzMatrix(int[][] matrix) {
        // Write your code here
        int m = matrix.length;
        int n = matrix[0].length;
        for(int g = 0; g<n; g++){
            for(int i = 0, j = i+g; j < n-1; i++,j++){
                if(i+1 <m && j+1 < n && matrix[i][j]!=matrix[i+1][j+1]) return false;
            }
        }
         for(int g = -1; g>-m; g--){
            for(int i = -g, j = i+g; i < m-1; i++,j++){
                if(i+1 <m && j+1 < n && matrix[i][j]!=matrix[i+1][j+1]) return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}

